title: Tahiti Cup
text:
The Tahiti Cup (also known as Coupe de Polynésie or Coupe de Tahiti Nui) is the premier <a href="association%20football">football</a> knockout tournament in <a href="French%20Polynesia">French Polynesia</a>. It was created in 1938, and gives the winner of the tournament a berth in the <a href="Coupe%20de%20France">Coupe de France</a>.
Between the years 2001 and 2006 two cup competitions were held in parallel.
